40|$|Satellite <b>emergency</b> <b>locator</b> {{systems were}} studied. The {{objective}} {{of the study was}} to determine the feasibility and hardware requirements for satellite systems capable of identifying and locating the position <b>emergency</b> <b>locator</b> transmitters and <b>emergency</b> position indicating radio beacons. Both geosynchronous and near-polar-orbiting satellites were considered. One of the most important aspects {{of the study was to}} minimize the cost of the hardware required...|$|R
