5000|$|Rescuers {{recommend}} that climbers carry a signaling device {{for use in}} emergencies. Signaling devices can include an MLU, Personal <b>Locator</b> <b>Beacon</b> (PLB), SPOT GPS Satellite Messenger, or 2-way radio (such as a HAM-radio), or cell phone.|$|R
40|$|In this study, the design, {{hardware}} {{implementation and}} characterisation of a self-tuning 406 MHz antenna of a Cospas-Sarsat personal <b>locator</b> <b>beacon</b> are presented. The realised prototype {{is able to}} perform automatic tuning of the antenna under time-varying environmental conditions due to human body movements and sea water proximity. The impedance tuning is performed by tracking the instantaneous value of the reflection coefficient and by modifying an appropriate impedance matching network according to a real-time adaptive algorithm. A resilient default/backup software architecture {{has been designed to}} ensure that tuning guarantees a return loss higher than 10 dB for the personal <b>locator</b> <b>beacon</b> in most of impedance mismatching conditions...|$|R
